sql:
SELECT Conference_Name
FROM (
    SELECT c.Conference_Name, COUNT(DISTINCT cp.staff_ID) AS attendants_count,
           DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY COUNT(DISTINCT cp.staff_ID) DESC) AS rank
    FROM conference c
    JOIN conference_participation cp ON c.Conference_ID = cp.Conference_ID
    GROUP BY c.Conference_Name
) ranked_conferences
WHERE rank <= 2;
question: Find the name of the conferences that have the top 2 most number of attendants.

sql:
SELECT Conference_Name
FROM conference c
JOIN (
    SELECT Conference_ID, COUNT(DISTINCT staff_ID) AS attendants_count
    FROM conference_participation
    GROUP BY Conference_ID
    ORDER BY attendants_count DESC
    LIMIT 2
) top2 ON c.Conference_ID = top2.Conference_ID;

sql:
SELECT Conference_Name
FROM conference c
JOIN (
    SELECT Conference_ID, COUNT(staff_ID) AS attendants_count
    FROM conference_participation
    GROUP BY Conference_ID
) cp ON c.Conference_ID = cp.Conference_ID
ORDER BY attendants_count DESC
LIMIT 2;
